    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-9",
      "detail": "4th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "In the dim dawn of another AL East scrap, the Blue Jays clawed back from the brink Monday night, turning a <strong>9-7 gut-check win over the Brewers</strong> into their first breath of momentum after dropping three of four &mdash; including that brutal 2-8 Twins thud last weekend. At 7-9, they're hunkered in fourth, three games back with a playoff seed of 11 and a fragile one-game streak that feels like borrowed time. Vlad Guerrero Jr. loomed large in the chaos, his bat a sledgehammer amid the rally, while Daulton Varsho &mdash; the Wisconsin kid facing his home-state crew &mdash; sparked the fire with timely hits that silenced the Milwaukee skid. No major injuries derailing the lineup yet, but the rotation's whispers of inconsistency linger like April chill. Tonight's rubber match at 6:40 PM ET against the Brewers' prodigy Jacob Misiorowski tests if this spark ignites or fizzles &mdash; <strong>win the series, and belief creeps in; drop it, and the East's wolves close ranks</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
