    "raptors": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Raptors",
      "league": "NBA",
      "record": "46-36",
      "detail": "3rd in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors clawed their way back from the brink, refusing to let another season slip into the abyss of mediocrity. <strong>Scottie Barnes erupted for 32 points and 12 rebounds in Monday's gritty 112-108 win over the Knicks</strong>, a statement that silenced doubters and snapped a mini-slump just as the calendar flipped to mid-April. At 46-36, they're riding a W1 streak into the postseason, holding third in the Atlantic Division and the <strong>No. 5 seed in the East</strong> &mdash; five games clear of the pack below, though a distant 14 games behind the division leaders. Barnes, the 24-year-old cornerstone, has been a force &mdash; averaging 28 over his last five outings &mdash; while Immanuel Quickley's sharpshooting (42% from deep this month) has masked Gary Trent Jr.'s trade-departure hangover. No major injuries clouding the horizon; this group's finally meshing under Darko Rajakovic's steady hand. The ghosts of rebuild years fade. <strong>Watch the play-in opener Friday against the Heat</strong> &mdash; win, and it's a first-round date with the elite; stumble, and the summer beckons early. Toronto's built for this fire now. Don't look away.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
