      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The off-season haze clings to Washington like a bad hangover, the Commanders' faithful nursing wounds from a 5-12 gut-punch that left them <strong>third in the NFC East</strong>, nine games adrift and staring down playoff seed 14. But here's the flicker: that gritty 24-17 gut-check win over the Eagles on Jan. 4 snapped a skid, their first W in a month after Dallas and Philly piled on the hurt &mdash; now riding a one-game streak into the void. Jayden Daniels, the rocket-armed savior, lit up Philly for 280 yards and two scores, his legs a blur that masked a line still leaking like a sieve; no major injuries, but whispers of a trade for edge help swirl as free agency drags. Dan Quinn's squad showed spine when it mattered least, stealing pride from rivals who'd long tuned them out. The real reckoning? <strong>The 2026 NFL Draft in two weeks</strong>, where they hold a top-10 pick &mdash; snag a lockdown corner like LSU's Mansoor Delane at No. 7, and this rebuild ignites; whiff, and it's another winter of what-ifs.",
